wikipedia_page.main: Charles Agar (20 May 1877 – 10 November 1921) was an English first-class cricketer. He was a right-handed batsman and a right-arm medium-pace bowler who played for Leicestershire. He was born in Rothley and died in Southfields, Leicester.
